  "title": "Pressure and Energy of Gas",
  "concepts": [
    {
      "title": "Pressure",
      "conceptBody": "<h3><strong>Pressure</strong></h3><p>Consider $\\text{Na}$ molecules, each of mass $\\text{m}$ enclosed in a spherical volume as shown.</p><p>Now the molecules moving with a velocity $\\text{v}$ as shown collide with the walls of container. Hence their change in momentum is given by</p><p>$\\Delta\\text{ p}=\\left( 2\\text{mv} \\cos\\theta \\right)$</p><p>the time between 2 collisions with the wall of the container can be given by$\\Delta t=\\left( \\frac{2R\\cos\\theta }{\\text{v}} \\right)$</p><p>$\\therefore {{\\text{F}}_{1}}=\\left( \\frac{\\Delta \\text{ p}}{\\Delta \\text{ t}} \\right)=\\frac{2\\text{mv} \\cos\\theta }{2\\text{R} \\cos\\theta }\\text{v}=\\left( \\frac{\\text{m}{{\\text{v}}^{2}}}{\\text{R}} \\right)$</p><p>Total force exerted $=\\frac{\\text{m}}{\\text{R}}\\left( \\text{v}_{1}^{2}+\\text{v}_{2}^{2}+\\text{v}_{3}^{2}+\\ldots \\text{v}_{\\text{n}}^{2} \\right)$</p><p>$=\\frac{\\text{m}\\times \\text{N}}{\\text{R}}\\left( \\text{v}_{\\text{rms}}^{2} \\right)$</p><p>$\\therefore$ Pressure exerted $=\\frac{\\text{m}\\times \\text{N}}{\\left( 4\\pi {{\\text{R}}^{2}} \\right)\\cdot \\text{R}}\\text{v}_{\\text{rms}}^{2}$</p><p>$P=\\frac{\\left( mN \\right)v_{rms}^{2}}{\\left( 4\\pi {{R}^{3}} \\right)}$</p><p><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" width=\"203\" height=\"189\"></p><p>$\\text{P}=\\frac{\\left( \\text{mN} \\right)}{3\\times \\left( \\frac{4}{3}\\pi {{\\text{R}}^{3}} \\right)}\\text{v}_{\\text{rms}}^{2}=\\frac{1}{2}\\left( \\frac{\\text{mN}}{\\text{V}} \\right)\\text{v}_{\\text{rms}}^{2}\\text{ (Kinetic }\\text{ equation }\\text{ of }\\text{ gas) }$</p><p>$\\text{P}=\\frac{1}{3}\\left( \\frac{\\text{mN}}{\\text{V}} \\right)\\text{v}_{\\text{rms}}^{2}=\\frac{1}{3}\\rho \\text{v}_{\\text{rms}}^{2}=\\frac{1}{3}\\left( \\frac{{\\text{{M}'}}}{\\text{V}} \\right)\\text{v}_{\\text{rms}}^{2}$</p>",
      "position": 0,
      "qcConcept": "66a0db56c03b9dcaf1afe14b"
    },
    {
      "title": "Kinetic Energy of gas",
      "conceptBody": "<h3>Kinetic Energy of a Gas</h3><p>Avg. translational KE of each molecule</p><p>$=\\frac{\\frac{1}{2}\\text{ }\\!\\!~\\!\\!\\text{ m}\\left( \\text{v}_{1}^{2}+\\text{v}_{2}^{2}+\\ldots \\text{v}_{\\text{n}}^{2} \\right)}{\\text{N}}$</p><p>$=\\frac{1}{2}\\text{ }\\!\\!~\\!\\!\\text{ mv}_{\\text{rms}}^{2}=\\frac{1}{2}\\text{ }\\!\\!~\\!\\!\\text{ m}\\left( \\frac{3\\text{KT}}{\\text{m}} \\right)=\\left( \\frac{3}{2}\\text{KT} \\right)$</p><p>$\\therefore \\text{ }\\!\\!~\\!\\!\\text{ }$ Avg. translational $\\text{KE}$ of each molecule $=\\left( \\frac{3}{2}\\text{KT} \\right)$</p><p>Now, $\\text{ }\\!\\!~\\!\\!\\text{ }\\frac{3}{2}\\text{KT}=\\frac{1}{2}\\text{ }\\!\\!~\\!\\!\\text{ m}\\left( \\text{v}_{\\text{rms}}^{2} \\right)$</p><p>$=\\frac{1}{2}m\\frac{\\left[ \\left( v_{1x}^{2}+v_{2x}^{2}+v_{3x}^{2}+\\ldots v_{x}^{2} \\right)+\\left( v_{1y}^{2}+\\ldots .+v_{ny}^{2} \\right) \\right]}{N}$</p><p>Now, due to random motion</p><p>$\\left[\\left\\langle v_x^2\\right\\rangle=\\left\\langle v_y^2\\right\\rangle=\\left\\langle v_z^2\\right\\rangle\\right]$</p><p>$\\Rightarrow \\quad \\frac{3}{2} \\mathrm{KT}=\\frac{1}{2} \\mathrm{~m}&lt;\\mathrm{v}_{\\mathrm{x}}^0&gt;+\\frac{1}{2} \\mathrm{~m}&lt;\\mathrm{v}_{\\mathrm{y}}^2&gt;+\\frac{1}{2} \\mathrm{~m}&lt;\\mathrm{v}_{\\mathrm{z}}^2&gt;$</p><p>$\\therefore \\quad \\frac{1}{2} \\mathrm{~m}&lt;\\mathrm{v}_{\\mathrm{x}}^2&gt;=\\frac{1}{2} \\mathrm{~m}&lt;\\mathrm{v}_{\\mathrm{y}}^2&gt;\\frac{1}{2}&lt;\\mathrm{v}_{\\mathrm{z}}^2&gt;=\\left(\\frac{1}{2} \\mathrm{KT}\\right)$</p>",
      "position": 1,
      "qcConcept": "66a0db56c03b9dcaf1afe14c"
    },
    {
      "title": "Equipartition of Energy",
      "conceptBody": "<h3><strong>Law of Equipartition of Energy&nbsp;</strong></h3><p>On average, $\\left( \\frac{1}{2}\\text{KT} \\right)$ energy can be associated with each degree of freedom.</p>",
      "position": 2,
      "qcConcept": "66a0db56c03b9dcaf1afe14d"
    }
  ],
